e for the Syrian army to move into the slums to disarm the two militias. <LOCATION> Syria </LOCATION>'s military intelligence chief in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>, Brig. Gen. <PERSON> Ghazi </PERSON> <PERSON> Kenaan </PERSON>, met with leaders of both warring factions as well as government and religious figures today. <LOCATION> Syria </LOCATION> deployed 7,500 troops in Moslem west <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION> in February 1987 to end militia warfare in the capital. It has not sent its forces into the southern slums, a traditional Hezbollah stronghold.
