<HEAD>Fire Erupts in Electric Plant, Causing Roof to Collapse</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALATKA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A fire whose smoke was visible for 40 miles roared through a coal-powered electric plant near here today, causing a roof to collapse, but no serious injuries were reported. The extent of damages in the $ 1.2 billion plant, which opened in 1984, was unclear, said fire dispatcher <PERSON> Miller </PERSON> <PERSON> Norton </PERSON>. No disruption in service to utility customers was expected. The fire erupted in a system that keeps hydrogen gas from escaping into the atmosphere, according to <PERSON> Jeff </PERSON> <PERSON> Fela </PERSON>, public affairs representative for <ORGANIZATION> Seminole </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electric </ORGANIZATION>. Hydrogen gas is a standard coolant for electric generators. One person, believed a worker at the <ORGANIZATION> Seminole </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electric </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cooperative </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Plant </ORGANIZATION>, was treated at the scene for unknown injuries, said Capt. <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> White </PERSON>, shift commander at the <ORGANIZATION> Palatka </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>. Another person earlier unaccounted for was found, <PERSON> Norton </PERSON> said. A plume of smoke was visible in <LOCATION> Jacksonville </LOCATION>, about 40 miles north of the plant. At least 30 fire units from the local department and surrounding counties were called to the scene after the fire was reported about 5 a.m., <PERSON> White </PERSON> said. More than 100 fire, rescue and law enforcement officers were called to help battle the blaze. `` It is contained from what we are told,'' Major <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Usina </PERSON> with the <ORGANIZATION> Putnam </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sheriff </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Office </ORGANIZATION> said shortly after 9 a.m. The two coal-fired generators where the fire erupted are locat