ainst big business and the establishment. In an effort to cater to true movie lovers, the organizers have even restricted the presence of television at this year's festival. Critics said the 1987 festival became a vehicle for the small screen. Many televised variety shows used the festival as a backdrop. Said Viot: `` We do not want the festival to become the battleground for a -LRB- television -RRB- ratings war.''
