on to <PERSON> Mitterrand </PERSON>, said <LOCATION> Switzerland </LOCATION>'s independent <PERSON> Le </PERSON> <PERSON> Matin </PERSON>, `` there was nothing but unrest, divisions, sectarianism and demagogy.'' In the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>, leader <PERSON> Mikhail </PERSON> <PERSON> Gorbatchev </PERSON> hailed <PERSON> Mitterrand </PERSON>'s success and expressed a wish for `` our personal contacts to play their positive role in promoting disarmament, building the common European house, settling regional conflicts, building trust, and improving the international climate on the whole.''
