<BYLINE>By LLOYD WILLIAMS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>KINGSTON, Jamaica (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An earthquake shook <LOCATION> Jamaica </LOCATION> shortly before noon Monday, rocking buildings in <LOCATION> Kingston </LOCATION> and sending frightened residents fleeing into the street. There were no reports of deaths and police said only one injury was reported. They said <PERSON> Natalie </PERSON> <PERSON> Thompson </PERSON>, 14, suffered broken ankles when she jumped in panic from the second floor of the <ORGANIZATION> Rosemount </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Linstead </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Catherine </LOCATION>, 40 miles northwest of the capital of <LOCATION> Kingston </LOCATION>. Officials said they had no reports of significant structural damage but the Office of Disaster Preparedness is conducting an island-wide survey of bridges and buildings. The Seismic Research Unit at the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> the </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Indies </ORGANIZATION> recorded the quake at 11:24 a.m. -LRB- EDT -RRB- and said its center was in the <LOCATION> Caribbean </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Sea </LOCATION> about 75 miles northeast of <LOCATION> Montego </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bay </LOCATION> and 15 miles south of the Cuban communities of <PERSON> Pilon </PERSON> and <PERSON> Portillo </PERSON>. It said the earthquake measured 4.2 degrees on the <PERSON> Richter </PERSON> scale. The university said the worst earthquake recorded in <LOCATION> Jamaica </LOCATION> was on Jan. 14, 1907, when <LOCATION> Kingston </LOCATION> was virtually destroyed. More than 1,000 people were killed and 9,000 were left homeless. The Richter scale is a gauge of energy released by a quake as recored on seismographs. A tremor registering 4 is capable of causing moderate damage and one with a magnitude of 5 can cause considerable damage. A quake recorded at 7 is considered a major quake.
