</TEXT>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Here is a list of some of the women who became important world leaders: <PERSON> Golda </PERSON> <PERSON> Meir </PERSON>, prime minister of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>, 1969-74. <PERSON> Indira </PERSON> <PERSON> Gandhi </PERSON>, prime minister of <LOCATION> India </LOCATION>, 1966-77 and 1980-84. <PERSON> Gro </PERSON> <PERSON> Harlem </PERSON> <PERSON> Brundtland </PERSON>, prime minister of <LOCATION> Norway </LOCATION>, 1981 and 1986-present. <PERSON> Corazon </PERSON> <PERSON> Aquino </PERSON>, president of <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Philippines </ORGANIZATION>, 1986-present. <PERSON> Isabel </PERSON> <PERSON> Peron </PERSON>, president of <LOCATION> Argentina </LOCATION>, 1974-76. Vigdis Finnbogadottir, president of <LOCATION> Iceland </LOCATION>, 1980-present. <PERSON> Margaret </PERSON> <PERSON> Thatcher </PERSON>, prime minister of <LOCATION> Great </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>, 1979-present. <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Eugenia </PERSON> <PERSON> Charles </PERSON>, prime minister of <LOCATION> Dominica </LOCATION>, 1980-present. <PERSON> Sirimavo </PERSON> <PERSON> Bandaranaike </PERSON>, prime minister of <LOCATION> Sri </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lanka </LOCATION>, 1960-65 and 1970-77. Reigning female monarchs: <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> II </PERSON> of <LOCATION> England </LOCATION>, 1952-present. <PERSON> Margrethe </PERSON> II of <LOCATION> Denmark </LOCATION>, 1972-present. <PERSON> Beatrix </PERSON> of <LOCATION> The </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Netherlands </LOCATION>, 1980-present: Ceremonial heads of state: <PERSON> Agtha </PERSON> <PERSON> Barbara </PERSON>, president of <LOCATION> Malta </LOCATION>, 1982-present. <PERSON> Jeanne </PERSON> <PERSON> Suave </PERSON>, governor-general of <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION>, 1985-present.
