<HEAD>Staley In Buyout Negotiations To Thwart British Bid</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: INSERTS 2 new grafs after 5th graf pvs The company... to
UPDATE with court rulings. Picks up 6th graf, Industry analysts...</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By DAVID DISHNEAU</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ROLLING MEADOWS, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Staley </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, seeking to thwart a $ 1.42 billion takeover bid by British sugar refiner <ORGANIZATION> Tate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Lyle </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION>, said Monday it was negotiating with at least one other party interested in acquiring part or all of the company. <PERSON> Staley </PERSON>, the nation's second-largest refiner of corn syrup and a leading producer of food-service supplies, said last week it had discussed selling all or part of the company to third parties and expected to enter into such negotiations. <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Satterfield </PERSON>, a spokesman for <PERSON> Staley </PERSON>, would not identify the parties. `` The significance here is that we've commenced negotiations,'' he said. `` There is a significant difference between discussions and negotiations.'' The company also said it would continue to explore other options to enhance shareholder value, including a financial restructuring or recapitalization, a joint venture or a leveraged buyout. In a leveraged buyout, the acquirer finances the purchase of the target company with sales of assets of the target or from its cash flow. Also Monday, <PERSON> Staley </PERSON> officials said the <ORGANIZATION> Delaware </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chancery </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> had upheld the validity of the company's shareholder-rights plan and other measures taken to defend against the <ORGANIZATION> Tate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Lyle </PERSON> takeover bid. Company officials also said a <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> upheld the constitutionality of the <LOCAT