ncois </PERSON> <PERSON> Mitterrand </PERSON> in the presidential election. The dollar fell to 5.7075 francs from 5.7230 francs. Other late dollar rates compared with late Friday included: 1.6820 marks, up from 1.6805; 1.4010 Swiss francs, down from 1.4015; 1.8805 Dutch guilders, down from 1.8860; 1,250.00 Italian lire, down from 1,254.00; 1.2396 Canadian dollars, up from 1.2375. In <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION>, where the business day ends as <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>'s begins, the dollar slipped 0.01 yen to a closing 124.87 yen. Later, in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, it was quoted slightly lower at 124.82 yen. Gold sold in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> at a late bid price of $ 444.00 a troy ounce, up from late Friday's $ 442.10. In <LOCATION> Zurich </LOCATION>, the late bid price was $ 445.00, up from $ 443 late Friday. Earlier, in <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION>, gold rose 79 cents to close at a bid $ 446.66. Silver was quoted in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> at a late bid price of $ 6.43 a troy ounce, up from Friday's $ 6.36.
