<HEAD>IBM Announces Half-Micron Chips</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By PETER COY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Business </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Machines </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said Monday it had produced the first fully functioning computer chips to have features measuring just a half micron across. The microscopically compact chips were made for the <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> by <ORGANIZATION> IBM </ORGANIZATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Systems </ORGANIZATION> facility in <LOCATION> Manassas </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>, the company said. They will be used for such things as capturing and processing radar and sonar signals. `` This is a significant technological milestone for <ORGANIZATION> IBM </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION>,'' <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Gianopulos </PERSON>, laboratory director of <ORGANIZATION> IBM </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Manassas </LOCATION>, said in a news release. `` <ORGANIZATION> IBM </ORGANIZATION> is leading the pack,'' <PERSON> Sonny </PERSON> <PERSON> Maynard </PERSON>, the director of the <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Very </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> High </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Speed </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Integrated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Circuit </ORGANIZATION> program, said in the release. <ORGANIZATION> Honeywell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> TRW </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, the other two companies that have defense contracts to develop half-micron chips, have not completed theirs yet. <ORGANIZATION> TRW </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Timothy </PERSON> <PERSON> Dolan </PERSON> said the company was on schedule toward a September 1989 deadline on its self-healing `` super chip,'' which will have about 4 million transistors, compared to about 100,000 for <ORGANIZATION> IBM </ORGANIZATION>'s chip. <ORGANIZATION> Honeywell </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman <PERSON> Susan </PERSON> <PERSON> Eich </PERSON> said her company was also on schedule. Compact chips run faster because the electricity has less distance to travel. A micron is one-millionth of a meter, or about one-hundredth the thickness of a sheet of typing paper. <ORGANIZATION> IBM </ORGANIZATION>'s contract with the <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> restricts how <ORGANIZATION> IBM </ORGANIZATION> can use the half-micron technology for its commercial products, spokesman <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Root </PERSON> said. Chip companies such as <ORGANIZATION> Intel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Advanced </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Micro </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Devices </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> are planning new fabrication lines for half-micron chips, according to <PERSON> Scott </PERSON> <PERSON> Hudson </PERSON>, a market research analyst for <ORGANIZATION> Integrated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Circuit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Engineering </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Scottsdale </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ariz. </LOCATION> `` This is what all the semiconductor makers are shooting for,'' <PERSON> Hudson </PERSON> said.
</TEXT>
